mintupdate (1:6.1.5~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix mainline kernel updates getting installed during a self-update
  * Inhibit refreshing also while the integrated kernel manager is showing
  * Remove the welcome screen, it provided little of value
  * Fix the icon for regular updates not rendering correctly on some platforms
    due to a bug in libgtk 3.24
  * Update translations

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sat, 11 Jan 2020 12:01:08 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.1.4~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update or kernel installation now inhibit refreshing for performance
    reasons, the refresh will be delayed until the installation has completed
  * Kernel Manager:
    * Remove titlebars from confirmation dialogs, adjust and normalize margins
    * Standalone version: Do not grey out the window while installing/removing
  * mint-release-upgrade: split off to its own source package
  * Update translations

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Mon, 30 Dec 2019 21:10:03 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.1.2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix a dismissed Linux Mint point release upgrade notification returning
    with each refresh until the application gets restarted
  * Update Ukranian translations

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Thu, 19 Dec 2019 13:37:05 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.1.1~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix several regressions with mainline kernel updates as far as end of life,
    release candidate and daily build-type mainline kernels are concerned
  * Reword regular kernel update description and replace Kernel Manager info
    window content with most of the same text
  * Preferences: Remove the option to show descriptions, it suffices to have it
    in the View menu
  * Fix interaction of some keybinds with lock-type modifier keys
  * Update translations

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Mon, 16 Dec 2019 18:53:21 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.1.0~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Automatic Updates:
    * Add optional support for creating a system snapshot (see Preferences)
    * Add optional support for mainline kernel updates (see Preferences)
    * Fix the "Unable to init server: Could not connect: Connection refused"
      message in the log
    * Significantly reduce log verbosity
  * Automatic Maintenance: significantly reduce log verbosity
  * mintupdate-cli:
    * automatically elevate privileges on upgrade, if necessary
    * shows help text instead of an error if run without arguments
    * Add --quiet option to reduce output verbosity
    * Add -m, --mainline option to enable mainline kernel support
    * Add -t, --create-snapshot option to create a system snapshot
  * Preferences/Ignore List:
    * The ignore list now lists packages put on a system-wide hold via the
      package management system. These are tagged with [apt hold] in the list.
      You can remove a hold by removing the entry from the list but there is
      intentionally no support for adding a hold since the preference is for
      you to use Update Manager's ignore list functionality.
    * The add to ignore list form can now be confirmed/closed by pressing Enter
  * Preferences/Automation:
    * Fix a failure to disable an automation feature resulting in a duplication
      of the Last Run/Next Run entries.
    * Fix a failure to set an Automatic Updates option leading to incorrect
      checkbox toggle states
  * Preferences/Expert: Fix toggling mainline kernel support not triggering
    a refresh of the list of updates
  * Rewrite mirror check on remote refresh, add desktop notification in case of
    unavailable or stale mirror.
    Note that the mirror check requires software-sources to be installed and
    is currently only performed on Linux Mint/LMDE platforms.
  * Add support for non-standard apt history log locations
  * Improve the wording of some error messages
  * Fix cursor type not getting updated during refresh with the window hidden
  * Fix regression with the ignore list export prompt crashing
  * Update translations

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 10 Dec 2019 22:57:51 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.0.5~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  IMPORTANT: 1:6.0.0~gm10 cannot self-update due to an oversight. To upgrade
             from that version please copy & paste this into a terminal window
             and run it:

                mintupdate exit && sudo apt-get install -y mintupdate

             Sorry about that!

  * Fix the fix on Mint...

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 01 Dec 2019 22:00:34 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.0.3~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix a crash on foreign platforms

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 01 Dec 2019 20:45:59 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.0.2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Do not disable the File menu and the Quit tray menu entry when on the
    self-update screen
  * Disable overlay scrolling for the update listing, the horizontal scrollbar
    can prevent clicking on an update entry
  * Kernel Manager:
      * Add menu button to upper right, remove reboot button and move
        functionality there, add additional reboot options and an option to set
        the default kernel. The "Reboot to another kernel" option once again
        filters out the current kernel, for that is now a separate option.
        Note that the menu only shows up if you're using GRUB and have more
        than one kernel installed.
      * Fix reboot to kernel functionality for liquorix kernels
      * Requests to open Kernel Manager from Update Manager will be ignored if
        the stand-alone version of Kernel Manager is already running
      * Changing Kernel Manager related preferences in Update Manager while a
        stand-alone Kernel Manager is running will update Kernel Manager's
        preferences view as well (the inverse is not true).
        However, a refresh made necessary by the changes will only happen if
        Kernel Manager's preferences are showing or get shown afterwards.
      * Fix toggling the checkbox to allow installation of different kernel
        flavors having no effect on a running Kernel Manager
      * Remove the upgrade eol series checkbox from the stand-alone version's
        preferences since it only affects Update Manager
      * Fix crash in stand-alone version when trying to display a certain error
        message
  * Mainline kernels:
    * Fix series updates to .0 versions failing
    * Fix some changelogs not being shown
    * Show short logs also for released kernels to keep it consistent with
      regular kernels. You can look up the detailed changelogs on kernel.org
  * History of Updates:
    * Open centered on the main window, if applicable
    * Open immediately and show a status page while loading the contents (same
      as main and Kernel Manager windows)
  * Fix main toolbar buttons not always being in the correct state
  * Fix self-update changelog getting re-downloaded on every refresh
  * Preferences: Change default value for recurring refresh from 2 to 6 hours
  * Add actions to the .desktop file mirroring the tray menu
  * Add show-preferences CLI command
  * Reword misleading right-click ignore menu entry
  * Update translations and fix update size units not getting translated

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 01 Dec 2019 17:14:48 +0100

mintupdate (1:6.0.0~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Kernel Manager:
    * Rename from `Linux Kernels` to `Kernel Manager`
    * Remove Close button and further adjust sizing of some elements in the
      bottom row to reduce the overall window width
    * Kernel Manager is now also available as a stand-alone program from your
      menu, in addition to the usual access via Update Manager's Tools menu.
      Note that the command opens the integrated version of Kernel Manager if a
      running Update Manager is detected.
    * The Reboot to Another Kernel button no longer filters out the current
      kernel, so you can use it to reboot to the same kernel even when it is
      not configured as GRUB's default.
    * Fix missing error message when kernel installation/removal fails due to
      the package management system being locked
  * Set Update and Kernel Manager's names in gnome-shell's top bar
  * Authentication dialog title renamed to "Update and Kernel Manager"
  * Ignore list:
    * Rename blacklist to ignore list
    * Fix "Ignore the current update" when used with a mainline kernel actually
      ignoring all kernel updates
    * When ignore list changes, check if automatic updates are enabled and
      prompt the user whether to export the ignore list for the automatic
      update service to use
  * Preferences: Remove Close button, reduce window height, fix toggling the
    mainline eol uprade option not triggering a refresh
  * History of Updates entry in tray menu no longer gets disabled during
    refreshes and installations.
  * Refactor threading in the entire application, eliminate all instances of
    using the deprecated GDK locking mechanism and fix some threading issues
    along the way
  * CLI commands:
    * Add bash completion support
    * Add `show-kernels`, `show-history`, `show-log` commands
  * Packaging: Split into four binary packages so different components like
    `kernel-manager` or `mint-release-upgrade` can be installed separately.
  * Drop unused and deprecated mintupdate-tool binary
  * Update translations and manual pages
  * Other small fixes and optimizations

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 22 Nov 2019 23:30:40 +0100

mintupdate (1:5.9.4~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix several functions being broken due to a merge mistake
  * Fix online help being inaccessible due to a packaging mistake

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Wed, 13 Nov 2019 15:43:21 +0100

mintupdate (1:5.9.3~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix a crash bug due to two lines accidentally having switched places :P

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Wed, 13 Nov 2019 08:28:08 +0100

mintupdate (1:5.9.2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations, remove invalid help files for Creek language
  * Update and amend all manual pages. Note that I have never yet touched the
    online help available from the GUI since I forked the app - maybe updating
    it could be a community effort.
  * Automation:
    * Prevent both automatic upgrades and automatic maintenance from
      running at the same time
    * If the package management system is locked by another process at the time
      the upgrade or maintenance service starts, both of them will now wait for
      the package management system to become available instead of exiting
  * Kernel window: Add button to installed kernels indicating whether they can
    be automatically removed or not. Clicking the button will toggle the state.
  * Preferences: The checkbox for refreshing Software Manager's cache is now
    disabled if mintinstall is not installed
  * Add "show", "hide", "exit", "restart", and "refresh" CLI commands
  * Fix kernel window getting stuck in refreshing state in certain situations
  * Fix end-of-life mainline kernel upgrade not getting offered anymore if the
    kernel was still on the kernel.org front page (the change in 1:5.9.0 was
    only intended for the kernel window, not update selection)
  * Fix history window search
  * Fix changelog retrieval sometimes associating the wrong changelog with a
    package
  * Refactoring and optimizing, somewhat improve memory management

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 12 Nov 2019 22:04:17 +0100

mintupdate (1:5.9.1~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix toggling automatic upgrades in preferences potentially freezing the app

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Mon, 04 Nov 2019 02:16:20 +0100

mintupdate (1:5.9.0~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations
  * Mainline kernel end-of-life series are now included in the kernel window
    while they remain listed on kernel.org's front page, which is usually for
    a few weeks until the next series gets released.
    The main reason for this change is that the release of the last version in
    a series coincides with declaring it end-of-life, which meant you could
    never actually install said last version of the series via the kernel
    window because it would not show any end-of-life series.
  * Changes to kernel meta package selection:
    - Only meta packages that share an origin with the current kernel are
      suggested
    - Meta package selection is now conservative: when a meta of a higher
      kernel series has to be suggested, then it will no longer suggest the
      meta with the highest available series and instead the meta with the
      lowest available series that is higher than the current kernel. For
      example, on bionic, if you have a 4.18 kernel installed but no meta, then
      previously the linux-generic-hwe-18.04-edge package for currently the 5.3
      series would be suggested, instead now the linux-generic-hwe-18.04 meta
      for currently the 5.0 series will be suggested.
  * Fix regular kernel upgrade suggestion when no meta package is found
  * Fix changelog window width in some desktop environments
  * debian/control: Drop mintsystem dependency, the required settings have been
    moved to mint-common

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 03 Nov 2019 11:25:30 +0100

mintupdate (1:5.8.9~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations
  * Add "Show Update Manager" button to updates available and release upgrade
    desktop notifications
  * Automatic upgrade service tries to wait for a network to become available,
    may still fail on resume from sleep
  * Preferences: No longer hide automatic upgrade options while automatic
    upgrades are disabled, so they can be configured before enabling the
    service
  * Localize preferences window last/next run labels and date/time
  * Localize history window date column contents
  * Fix history window changelog display
  * Fix kernel window having non-localized "Supported until" label
  * Drop gettext dependency

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 27 Oct 2019 17:50:00 +0100

mintupdate (1:5.8.8~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations
  * Preferences:
    * The option to hide the application after an installation/removal
      completes now hides the application already when installation/removal
      begins
    * The option to warn if system snapshots are not set up was removed
    * Enabling automated system snapshots now requires Timeshift to be
      installed and set up, failing that an error message will be displayed.
      The same applies if Timeshift or its configuration are subsequently
      removed.
  * Fix snapshot failure detection, non-fatal errors will now be ignored
  * Mainline kernels: Release candiate series are no longer proposed as an
    upgrade even if you checked the option to include them. That option now
    only affects the contents of the kernel window. I realize this is
    functionality loss but after seeing some users on RC kernels without much
    reflection I am not comfortable anymore with offering this.
    You can, of course, still manually install a release candidate-series and
    will continue receiving updates for that.
  * Several changes for improved compatibility with non-Linux Mint platforms
  * Packaging: Remove mint-mirrors dependency (moved to mintsources), add
    Timeshift to recommends

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 13 Oct 2019 11:45:28 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.7~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations
  * Automated snapshots now have a configurable maximum number to keep,
    additional snapshots will automatically be removed the next time you create
    an automated snapshot. Note that this only affects snapshots created after
    this update unless you manually add " #mintupdate" (without quotation
    marks) at the end of existing snapshot comments.
  * The preferences window now gets locked while changing certain options that
    take a moment to process
  * Packaging: Make sure some optional configuration files in /etc get removed
    on purge
  * Some refactoring

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 04 Oct 2019 18:34:27 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.6~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations
  * Do not disable Refresh options while on the self-update screen and not
    applying the self-update yet
  * Fix automatic self-update crash if the main window has not been shown yet
  * Fix not detecting some update installation errors - this also prevents an
    infinite automatic self-update loop in case of an undetected error
  * debian/control: Update depends

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 22 Sep 2019 21:38:11 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.5-1~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations
  * Prefences now have an option to toggle refreshing Software Manager's cache
    along with Update Manager's cache. This enabled by default (and was before)
    but you can disable it to only refresh Software Manager on demand and thus
    decrease the system load due to Update Manager's remote refreshes.
  * Status icon:
    * Fix handling of icon theme changes when not using AppIndicator
    * Fix the icon getting recreated on icon change and the first time the
      window gets shown when not using AppIndicator
  * History window:
    * Show foreign architecture in package name
    * Fix sorting of the first two columns when clicking the column headers
    * Add sort marker to date column on load to reflect how the list was
      already sorted
  * Release upgrader:
    * Use the user's theme and proxy settings
    * During the upgrade grey out and show a watch cursor
    * Remove mint-release-upgrade-root command
  * Packaging:
    * Fix a bug in preinst with upgrading from the official version via the
      command line without mintupdate running
    * Complete overhaul of the packaging in several other aspects, improving in
      particular the handling of remove, purge and downgrade operations
  * Right-click update ignore functionality now has a confirmation dialog to
    prevent accidental blacklisting
  * Use mintcommon.synaptic module

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 17 Sep 2019 00:59:41 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.4~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Update translations, Croation, Dutch, German and Russian are complete!
    If you want to help out with your language(s), head to:
    https://translations.launchpad.net/gm10-linuxmint-tools
  * History of Updates window now supports selecting multiple entries that can
    be copied with Ctrl+c in a space separated format for paste into a
    spreadsheet application, for example
  * Preferences window:
    * Add dropdown for selecting the default update details tab, replacing the
      previous checkbox
    * Rename Refresh tab to "Refresh Schedule", reword labels accordingly and
      add further explanatory text
  * Preferences, kernel, shortcuts and  mainline installer windows are no
    longer modal, i.e. interaction with other windows is possible again
  * Main application log add year to date format
  * Log View window slimmed down to the essential only: the log contents
  * Fix an error with opening log and history windows while already open
  * Mirror checking no longer uses pycurl
  * Do not check mirror staleness during local refreshs
  * debian/control: update dependencies

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 10 Sep 2019 21:33:30 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.3~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix regression that broke automatic-updates, and a further bug with failure
    handling
  * Fix regression with self-update button and checkbox becoming sensitive
    again after update completes and before the app restarts
  * Remove some redundant code including special provision for KDE desktops to
    use AppIndiciator - KDE and other desktops not supporting StatusIcon can
    just select AppIndicator from Preferences.

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Mon, 02 Sep 2019 22:26:36 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix an issue with upgrading from the official LM19.2 version: The upgrade
    will now close all running mintupdate instances when upgrading from such a
    version (they will not restart automatically)
  * Preferences > Interface:
    * Add option to close the installation/removal popup window automatically
      - this is the current behaviour and enabled by default, but you can now
      disable this behaviour
    * Reword the option to hide the Update Manager window after upgrades, it
      now applies to kernel installations/removals as well
  * Mainline kernel installer:
    * Add download progressbar
    * Allow canceling downloads
    * Fix being able to close the installer window via the window menu event
      when the close button was hidden
    * Add status message for the "Verifying downloaded files" step
  * Kernel window: Show kernel flavor in install/remove confirmation dialog
  * Fix status icon not updating after icon theme changes when not using
    AppIndicator

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 27 Aug 2019 17:35:02 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.1~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fixed the icons to look correctly when rendered using the broken version of
    librsvg distributed with Mint 19/Ubuntu 18.04 - I'm not actually developing
    this on those releases and had not thought to check previously
  * Kernel window: Fix kernel operations failing if the main window had not
    been shown yet
  * Kernel window: Fix kernel meta-package not getting removed when removing
    all kernels of the same series at once and more than one was installed
  * Fix the popup when downloading/installing/removing updates and non-mainline
    kernels not using the user's theme
  * Add option to preferences to notify automatic update users about a failure
    to update or a requirement to reboot.
  * mintupdate-cli/automatic updates now create /run/reboot-required, where
    appropriate, allowing the main application to display a notification in
    those cases (this is separate from and potentially in addition to the
    automatic updates notifier mentioned above)
  * If the main window is minimized it is now considered hidden as far as the
    status icon is concerned (so clicking the icon will restore it)
  * Preferences window now behaves like the kernel window as far as window
    states are concerned, i.e. it is linked to the main window and does not
    appear in the window list in addition to the main window
  * Preferences window now opens centered on the main window
  * Preferences: Mainline kernel warning now specifically states that they lack
    the modification and additional drivers of the supported kernels
  * Unnecessary feature of the day:
    The main window now also remembers its position and will try to restore it.
    Due to timing issues the position may not be saved when quitting while the
    window is open. Also restoring the position will fail on display servers
    without global positioning, e.g. those using the Wayland protocol.

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 20 Aug 2019 12:00:36 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.8.0~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Toolbar slimmed down and uses custom icons to ensure a uniform presentation
  * Clean up other application-specific icons
  * Changelog display: Fix incomplete themes like Mint-X not defining a
    monospace font style class by defining it for them (this fixes issues with
    changelog display width calculation)
  * Changelog display: Work around themes potentially defining a non-monospace
    font as the monospace font by calculating the layout width based on the
    character "x" * 80.

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 16 Aug 2019 19:04:12 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.9~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix non-mainline kernel installation failing
  * Fix mainline kernel changelogs not getting displayed in the update details
    pane anymore.
  * Fix being able to add invalid refresh schedule values via dconf

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 13 Aug 2019 16:01:05 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.8~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix mainline kernel updates getting installed during a self-update

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 09 Aug 2019 20:41:20 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.7~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix self-update not restarting the application anymore after the last
    change (I knew I had forgotten something)

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 09 Aug 2019 20:01:13 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.6~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Starting another instance of Update Manager no longer kills the existing,
    instead it shows it. This prevents problems caused by killing the Update
    Manager process in the middle of an update and simply makes more sense.
  * Preferences > Automation now shows the last and next run times for enabled
    automation options
  * Add AppIndicator support for the tray icon. AppIndicator is supported by
    more desktop environments than the deprecated GtkStatusIcon that's in use
    by default. However, because AppIndicator is more limited in functionality
    (no left-click toggle, no tooltip) I made it optional for now, you can
    toggle it in Preferences.
  * The reboot required notification is now persistent across restarts of the
    application. The file /run/reboot-required gets created and can be used
    by other applications/scripts.
  * Fix system snapshot failure not getting detected with the latest version of
    Timeshift. Improve snapshot creation status messaging.
  * Kernel window: Now stays in front of the main window at all times and does
    not appear as a separate window in the panel anymore when both are showing.
    Because of that its visibility states are now largely linked to those of
    the main window. Bit of an experimental feature, wanting to preserve my
    panel real-estate.
  * Mainline kernel installer now stays in front of the main window and has its
    state linked but retains a separate panel entry
  * Mainline kernel installer now verifies the checksums of the downloaded
    files before installing them and fails if they do not match.
  * Kernel window: Release candidate mainline kernels have a changelog button
    as well now, showing the git commit log for lack of a real changelog
  * Kernels: Add support for Valve's experimental mfutex kernels
  * Non-Unicode locales: Work around a bug in python-apt that would break
    refreshing the list of updates in non-unicode environments with mainline
    kernels enabled. The app should be fully non-unicode compatible now,
    however relevant that may be. It will still spam a lot of unicode errors to
    stdout which come from python-apt and have to be fixed there, but they do
    not impede the operation of this app anymore.
  * Reboot to another kernel button is now only enabled when at least one other
    supported kernel is installed
  * Preferences: Fix mainline sub-options initially being visible even without
    enabled mainline support
  * Fix the self-update changelog box being sized incorrectly if the window was
    minimized while the changelog was retrieved

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 09 Aug 2019 19:00:23 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.5~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Kernel window now shows and supports installation of Liquorix ZEN kernels
    if available via your software sources (64-bit systems only).
    They have been integrated as a kernel flavor that you can select from the
    dropdown (you may need to enable kernel flavors on the Expert tab of
    Preferences first). Installed kernels of supported flavors do, of course,
    always show regardless of your selection and setting.
    Missing meta package will be installed automatically as with other flavors.
  * Kernel window now always shows your currently active kernel even if it is a
    kernel that's not otherwise shown/supported by the kernel window
  * Kernel operations now produce a log message for each involved kernel and
    meta package
  * Kernel window: Some optimization and fix capitalization of two buttons
  * Kernel window: Kernels no longer have a web browser link to the changelog
    but instead a button that will bring up a modal window with the changelog
  * Kernel window: Fix release candidate kernels having a changelog link
  * The tray icon menu's "Show" item now changes to "Hide" where appropriate
  * Trying to open log view or history window when they're already open results
    in them being brought to the foreground (and restored, if minimized)
  * Improved the way windows get brought into the foreground, this wasn't
    always fully reliable with all window managers
  * Fix being able to open log view multiple times
  * Fix a potential crash in the log view
  * Changelogs in self-update window and history window changelog view now use
    a monospaced font and the width gets set to 80 characters based on your
    font settings to ensure a consistent display on all platforms
  * Self-update changelog box height increased for better readability
  * Fix self-update changelog not showing unless automatically self-updating
  * Fix kernel meta packages depending on unversioned other meta-packages
    potentially resulting in an update listing showing the wrong new version.
  * Preferences window: Remove a tooltip that had ended up on the wrong widget
  * Fix a broken import in the release upgrader
  * Merge updated upstream translations, for whatever good it may do

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Thu, 01 Aug 2019 18:41:09 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.4~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix mainline kernel updates not showing (the fix from last version had been
    incomplete)
  * Fix crash/segfault in refresh thread
  * Fix some code potentially running unnecessarily in refresh thread

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 26 Jul 2019 17:10:21 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.3~gm10) bionic; urgency=high

  * Edit > System Snapshots and Edit > Software Sources have now been
    integrated into the common authentication system as well, they will now ask
    for authentication as Update Manager. This means you can now use all
    functions of Update Manager with only a single authentication.
  * Fix a regression in checkAPT after last update resulting in a refresh error
    when mainline kernels are enabled
  * Fix a typo causing the  automated system snapshots ask for confirmation
    option showing even when automated system snapshots are disabled
  * Kernel installation/removal error messages format adjuste to match the rest
    of the application

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Mon, 22 Jul 2019 17:28:27 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.2~gm10) bionic; urgency=high

  * Daily mainline kernel builds of types daily, drm-tip, drm-next or
    drm-intel-next will now receive updates after all. Installation of those
    types remains impossible from the kernel window but if you installed one in
    other ways the updates (if any) will be proposed.
  * Fix a critical bug with the authentication module not requesting
    authentication on an Ubuntu base anymore at all. Apparently Ubuntu only
    implements a limited version of pkexec which ignores argv1 annotations in
    security policies.
  * Fix mainline kernel installation return status not getting checked
    correctly in all cases
  * Improve error handling for some root-enabled functions

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Mon, 22 Jul 2019 00:12:10 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.1~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Don't show a desktop notification in case of an automatic self-update
  * Fix automatic self-update potentially running when it should not (to no
    effect)
  * Write a log message when automatic self-update runs

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 19 Jul 2019 20:34:20 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.7.0~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix clicking the self-update button not disabling the checkbox below

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 19 Jul 2019 19:35:36 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.9~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Self-updates are somewhat annoying, that's why they get another facelift:
    - the changelog is now shown on the self-update screen itself so you no
      longer have to find it in the history window after the update
    - authentication is no longer required - self-updates are not optional so
      it doesn't matter who installs them as long as they get installed.
    - you can choose to have self-updates performed automatically without user
      interaction in Preferences or right on the self-update page. It'll still
      pop up the synaptic window so you know it is happening.
    - The self-update button label apparently confused some users into thinking
      the computer would restart, this has been clarified
  * The list of updates now remembers which column you sorted by and even
    without custom sorting the default sort column gets marked as such rather
    than make the list appear unsorted, which it never is
  * Desktop notifications can now be disabled in preferences
  * Kernel window: Kernels from the -proposed pocket now get marked as
    "(Pre-release)" to make it easier to identify them. The "Unsupported"
    status alone was reportedly not clear enough of an indication. This now
    matches the option in Software Sources allowing you to enable "Pre-release"
    updates.
  * Kernel window: Fix the initial help screen not showing
  * Kernel window now specifically identifies certain mainline kernel builds
    in the status column, namely daily, drm-tip, drm-next and drm-intel-next.
  * Fix offering updates for above special mainline builds to regular versioned
    mainline builds. There is no support for installing and updating said
    builds for now, and unless somebody specifically asks for it there probably
    never will be (except for maybe the daily builds, I haven't decided).
  * Preferences slightly re-styled, and auto-refresh options are now on a
    separate Refresh tab
  * mint-refresh-cache: Fix exception in case of apt errors
  * Fix localization, seems this got broken a good while ago and nobody noticed
  * Many code quality and maintenance updates and few minor performance
    improvements

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 19 Jul 2019 15:28:08 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.8~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Improve reboot required notification to include more than kernel updates
  * Fix update details pane flashing up briefly after a refresh
  * Refactor and optimize kernel window and dpkg lock check
  * Refactor history window and log view
  * Remove some unnecessary code from RefreshThread
  * Merge upstream translation update, although this will only affect parts of
    the application
  * debian/control: update required mint-common version

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 12 Jul 2019 20:45:52 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.7~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Add option to automatically upgrade mainline kernels to the latest
    available released series when the installed mainline kernel's series has
    reached end of life. This option is enabled by default.
  * The log files now have proper file names including creation date and time
  * Work around encoding issue with localization in non-unicode environments
  * Work around a bug with the notification server on Mint leading to a
    formatting issue with the release upgrade notification

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Mon, 08 Jul 2019 21:33:40 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.6~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix a reboot required notification being given even if a mainline kernel
    download failed
  * Fix typo in mintupdate-cli manual
  * Release upgrade:
    - Merge code maintenance commit from upstream
    - Fix an exception in an exception handler
    - Fix not checking for update-grub success/return value
    - Some code quality improvements

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Tue, 02 Jul 2019 01:44:32 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.5+build3~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Kernel window: Fix bug with rebooting to the default kernel

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 14 Jun 2019 21:55:37 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.4+build2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Kernel window: Add a "Reboot to another kernel" button which allows you to
    reboot to a specific (installed) kernel. This will fail in cases where you
    are not using GRUB at all (the button should not even show then) or not
    from the current operating system, or if GRUB cannot write to the
    environment block, such as when it is stored on an MDRAID or LVM device.
    Feedback about how this feature is working out for you is appreciated. The
    worst that can happen in case of a failure is that you will reboot to your
    current kernel.
  * Authentication for preferences changes (automation features) now uses the
    common authentication handler introduced in 5.6.2 as well to further reduce
    the potential amount of authentications required in using the application
  * Automated system snapshots: In case of an error add the last line of output
    again to the final "System snapshot failed" status message and to the log
    so it remains available for review if the user only looks at it later
  * Include kernel packages to the History of Updates listing. Technically
    those are no upgrades except for the meta package but since mainline
    kernels have no meta package and also the kernel window allows installation
    of other kernels it makes sense to include them in the listing as part of
    the history of changes the application made to the system

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 14 Jun 2019 20:25:54 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.3~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Do not create a system snapshot before a self-update

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 07 Jun 2019 19:06:31 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Rework the update and kernel authentication system, you now have to
    authenticate only once for "Update Manager" (no longer "Synaptic") and that
    covers all steps of the process including snapshot creation, regular update
    and mainline kernel installation.
    Note that the system-configured maximum authentication cache duration still
    applies (by default 5 minutes) and if the overall process takes longer than
    that then you may be asked to authenticate again after all. This could be
    worked around but I'm not sure it's worth the complexity it would add.
  * Tray icon: Clicking on the icon or selecting the "Show" menu item no longer
    shows the main window while the kernel window is open. Instead the kernel
    window gets brought to the foreground.
  * Tray icon: Never make the "Show" menu item insensitive
  * Automated snapshots: Add option to show a confirmation dialog before
    creating a snapshot
  * Improve the description for Ubuntu kernel updates, explaining how to roll
    back a kernel
  * Mainline kernel installation: Improve error message in case no files to
    download could be found, assume build failure even if not indicated on the
    page, although it could theoretically be a parser failure
  * Slightly adjust main app log format
  * Fix installed release candidate mainline kernels not getting merged
    correctly into the list of available kernels
  * Fix automatic maintenance function including a (harmless) debconf error
    message in the logs
  * Fix status icon not reflecting installation status while mainline kernel is
    downloading
  * Fix mainline kernel installation not cleaning up a process handle

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 07 Jun 2019 18:38:46 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.1~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Load Software Sources and Timeshift, when launched via mintupdate under the
    current user's profile instead of the root user's profile, in particular
    including the current user's theme
  * Preferences: add option to default update details to Description instead of
    Packages
  * Fix update details pane not getting hidden again after a refresh
  * Add padding to error details text where applicable

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 02 Jun 2019 02:46:34 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.6.0+build2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Preferences: Adjusted the labels for the auto-refresh schedules and added a
    note explaining that you can set them to 0 to disable them individually
  * The items in the Tools menu now have keyboard shortcuts
  * Tray icon menu now has "Show" and "History of Updates" items
  * Make sure all windows get raised upon open so window managers do not
    sometimes open them in the background
  * Mainline kernel versions installed as updates (i.e. via the main window)
    can now automatically be removed in the same way as Ubuntu's kernels
    (does not apply to mainline kernel updates installed with previous versions
    of mintupdate)
  * mint-refresh-cache now updates mintinstall's cache as well (used to be
    handled by checkAPT before mint-refresh-cache had been created)
  * Some performance improvements, including removal of most instances of
    unnecessarily spawning a shell
  * Changed some notification icons
  * Some threading changes
  * Fix GUI sensitivity issues after canceled or failed self-update
  * Add a number of missing dependencies and drop a few unused ones
  * mintsystem >= 1:8.5.0 is now a dependency due to the changes to apt's
    configuration it makes that mintupdate relies upon

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Fri, 24 May 2019 23:40:40 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.9~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix mainline kernel installation via the kernel window that I broke in the
    last version.

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sat, 18 May 2019 09:17:01 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.8~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Rename File > "Close" menu item to "Hide" to clarify the functionality
  * Add File > Quit menu item
  * Updates listing: Fix right-click options having their descriptions switched
  * Updates listing: Move the column with the checkboxes first and remove the
    unnecessary header to save space, also make that column as well as the
    "Type" column unresizable
  * Show a desktop notification when a reboot is required, software updates, a
    self-update or a new point release are available
  * Preferences: Clarify that automated snapshots only apply to manual updates
    (as opposed to automatic updates) and that automatic updates do not include
    mainline kernels at this time (and possibly forever - you should not use
    these types of kernels unattended)
  * Kernel window: "Bug report" links renamed "Bug Tracker" and "CVE Tracker"
    links renamed to "Known Security Issues (CVE)"
  * Kernel window: Mainline kernels now also have CVE and Bug tracker links
  * Kernel window: Installed mainline kernels are identified based on the
    version string and now also show the same information as not-installed
    mainline kernels
  * About window rebrand from "mintUpdate" to "Update Manager" (localized) and
    change the link to point to my PPA
  * Adjust some automated refresh schedule timings

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Thu, 16 May 2019 20:18:13 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.7~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Disable Clear and Select All toolbar buttons when no updates are shown.
  * Only enable the Install toolbar button when an update is selected.
  * Add mainline kernel downloads and installations do now show a status
    window. This is not the final version because there is still a duality
    with usage of synaptic for other operations, so you (still) may have to
    authenticate twice. I remain undecided how I want to implement a combined
    version (rewrite aptdaemon and use that, write a new API, or simply use
    apt-get/dpkg in an integrated terminal as now for the mainline kernels).
  * Fix regression: mainline kernels list didn't get refreshed if previously
    cached
  * Fixed various bugs surrounding inline updates of mainline kernels that
    resulted from a merge error back when I created the public fork.

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 12 May 2019 18:10:20 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.6+build2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix regression: self-update button not getting disabled
  * Only show update details view when an update is selected
  * Slightly improve network performance of mainline kernels handling and
    add 5s timeouts to all network connection attempts.

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sat, 11 May 2019 15:45:01 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.5~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Kernelwindow: Fix window destroy handler not getting disconnected and
    preventing closing of the window in certain situations
  * Kernelwindow: Fix exception when closing the window while it is refreshing
  * Fix bug with a status message showing when it shouldn't and change code to
    prevent such issues for good
  * Fix regression with configured kernel type not always getting loaded

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Thu, 09 May 2019 01:05:52 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.4~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Drop the super broken code that replaced package descriptions with
    localized descriptions in a random available language for a semi-
    random package. This also fixes the bug where compressed repository files
    were not supported. Localized translations will now properly be displayed
    where available (same as apt would on the command line).
  * Fix short descriptions (in the update list) not being localized
  * Fix string decoding/unescaping issues for all descriptions
  * Fix refresh while minimized not retrieving localization data
  * Main window menu, toolbar and certain tray menu items will now selectively
    get disabled where they would interfere with another running operation or
    open window. The rest of the application remains accessible now.
  * Added option to hide longterm support mainline kernels because the large
    number of kernels in some of these series can slow the kernel window down
    and most users will only be interested in the latest "stable" or "mainline"
    series, anyway.
    The filter options have no impact on receiving updates for those kernels,
    you will receive them within the same series no matter
  * Fix regression with mainline kernel release candidate filtering

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Wed, 08 May 2019 20:30:06 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.3~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Move mainline release candidate checkbox to the preferences window
  * Slightly widen history changelog window

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 05 May 2019 21:02:45 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.2~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix bug with using the selection keybinds before the first refresh finished
  * Mainline kernels show "Status Unknown" if there was an error determining
    their support status
  * Fix a regression with and improve handling of exceptions related to
    mainline kernels
  * Fix an instance of the package cache getting deleted not being handled

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sun, 05 May 2019 14:07:49 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.1~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Fix status messages showing on self-update when reopening the window

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sat, 04 May 2019 17:55:14 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.5.0~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Mainline kernels no longer get filtered by minimum series and instead by
    support status, making older longterm support kernel series available
  * Fix and streamline origin name rewriting
  * Rewrite of auto-refresh scheduling:
    - initial refresh now also gets delayed, not skipped, while the application
      window is open
    - refresh schedules are now dynamic and get reloaded in regular intervals,
      allowing for changes to a refresh interval during the interval or while
      it is delayed
    - a manual refresh will reset the recurring schedule
    - system sleep and changes to system date/time are handled more reliably
  * Fix a bug with re-enabling the refresh schedules
  * Efficiency improvement: Always delete the auto-refresh thread when not
    needed, including where auto-refresh is enabled in preferences but no
    further refresh is actually scheduled
  * Better logging surrounding the auto-refresh thread

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Sat, 04 May 2019 16:25:01 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.4.9~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  * Change and greatly simplify the way the update description is selected
    from a multi-package update to hopefully provide the best possible
    update description from the available choices in all cases

 -- gm10 <gm10@quantentunnel.de>  Wed, 01 May 2019 03:41:08 +0200

mintupdate (1:5.4.8~gm10) bionic; urgency=medium

  [ gm10 ]
  * Add epoch to version to avoid collision with Mint's official packages.
  * Forked, major refactor including many fixes and improvements that won't be
    listed individually.
  * Add option for automated timeshift snapshots before applying updates (GUI
    only)
  * Changelogs v2, better and more complete changelog retrieval and right-click
    changelogs in history
  * Add option for enabling full mainline kernel support (installation GUI
    integration remains WIP)
  * Add option for enabling kernel flavor selection
  * Preferences: allow configuration of automatic upgrades service
  * Automatic upgrades use systemd instead of cron
  * Remove mintupdate-autoremove cron job
  * Blacklist: Allow right-click blacklisting of multiple source packages
    grouped as a single update (kernel packages)
  * Kernelwindow: Show refreshing status page and watch cursor while
    checkKernels.py is running similar to when the updates list is refreshing
  * Add status_refreshing page, major refactor of RefreshThread, status icon
    and message handling, infobar handling, and parts of InstallThread
  * Preferences refactor: Save and apply changes in realtime, refresh only for
    blacklist changes
  * Add installed size to packages tab
  * Kernelwindow: Show kernel flavour in currently using label (#537)
  * Kernelwindow: Assume Ubuntu kernels in the non -proposed pockets are
    supported even when Supported tag is missing (#539)
  * checkAPT: Fix two bugs in add_update (#538)
  * checkAPT: Rework source name grouping for kernel-type updates (#534)
  * checkAPT.py assorted fixes: Drop unused function, fix .keys() usage, remove
    unnecessary sorting (#528)
  * KernelVersion rework (#525)
  * Fix automatic upgrades default configuration (#530)
  * kernelwindow.py: Remove unused imports, variable and execute permissions
    (#526)
  * Drop "(local)" tag from non-repository installed kernels, it's not really
    relevant information and wasn't localized, anyway (#527)
  * mintupdate-cli: Don't define PRIORITY_UPDATES, import from Classes.py
    (#531)
  * Infobars: Only pad below (#533)
  * InstallThread: Don't hardcode MessageDialog default component names (#536)
  * kernels.ui: flavour > flavor (#529)
  * Remove unnecessary gi imports (#522)
  * Drop checkbutton_default_repo_is_ok (#524)
  * Check if timeshift exists in timeshift_check() (#523)
  * Run apt-config and apt-cache with LC_ALL=C (#521)
  * Kernel window: Ellipsis handling (#518)
  * Refactor RefreshThread to make it more readable (#517)
  * Add self-update status page (#507)
  * Preferences: Add description to automatic maintenance option (#501)
  * Blacklisting: Add user blacklist export button to preferences, (#499)
  * Add root_mode argument to refresh method, point all but one RefreshThread
    usages to this method (#506)
  * Simplify refresh subprocesses commands, do not  spawn a shell, do not use
    deprecated method (#503)
  * Kernel window: Add support for queueing actions (#509)
  * Normalize capitalization according to GNOME style guidelines (#514)
  * Kernel window: Automatically show flavour selector while multiple flavours
    are installed (#512)
  * Change question-type infobars to Yes/No buttons (#513)
  * Kernel window: Greatly speed up load times (#508)
  * CacheWatcher pause/resume changes in interaction with refresh and install
    threads (#505)
  * Preferences: Blacklist add separate version entry and descriptive labels
    (#502)
  * Fix checkWarnings still using removed dist-upgrade setting (#500)
  * Fix logging errors and make small optimizations (#498)
  * Improve mint-refresh-cache (#497)
  * Remove count from package list to avoid launchpad translation issues (#494)
  * Kernelwindow: Automatically remove left-over meta-packages (#455)
  * Fix changelog retrieval in last commit (#491)
  * Fix generic blacklisting of kernel packages (#490)
  * Add Packages tab and move package listing from descriptions tab there
    (#467)
  * Kernelwindow: Add optional kernel flavour selector (#457)
  * Add distribution end of life warning and status (#459)
  * Drop unnecessary except variables (#488)
  * Properly escape markup in updates listing (#489)
  * Change kernelwindow.py as well
  * Change datetime import
  * Preferences: Run recurring refresh timer based on last refresh time, (#462)
  * APT policy check: Reword error message when Mint layer wasn't found, (#483)
  * Remove old kernels: Only pre-select kernels older than the current one
    (#482)
  * Rework kernel/meta recommendation logic (#456)
  * Always show all applicable infobars, and all infobars to use show_infobar
    function (#479)
  * Fix root refresh creating root owned files and on LMDE ignoring settings
    (#472)
  * alias kernel updates only if meta or at least 3 packages in update (#464)
  * Refactor information window for compatibility with current Gtk version,
    also make read-only. (#486)
  * Information window use new Logger.read function (#476)
  * Add simple reboot notification for kernel updates (#478)
  * Rewrite Logger (#475)
  * Fix lsb_release calls (#477)
  * Prevent right-click blacklisting PRIORITY_UPDATES (#473)
  * Add manual pages (#468)
  * checkAPT: Only run mintinstall-update-pkgcache when root (#445)
  * Assorted fixes (#454)
  * Point to "apt update" on release information change (#453)
  * Automatically refresh Update Manager when the package cache is changed
    (#441)
  * Add issue templates
  * Revert remaining part of f0829ac04b559a76fed0639bf5590f80bd78bd8d, which
    is incompatible with my kernel window patches (#480)
  * kernelwindow: Support installed kernels of different types (#434)
  * Preferences and automation rework (#416)
  * Handle dpkg lock via fuser, remove existing process based detection code
    (#446)
  * Fix "Always show kernel updates" behaviour (#428)
  * Fix "Hide after applying updates" option (#430)
  * Allow blacklisting a specific version (#421)
  * checkWarnings.py: Fix indentation, coding style (#466)
  * kernelwindow: Reverse sort Remove old kernels (#450)
  * Kernelwindow: center on main window (#458)
  * Fix Gtk.MessageDialog "transient parent" issues (#449)
  * Prevent extraneous blank lines on error status (#443)

  [ Clement Lefebvre ]
  * Improve timeshift check
  * Fix checkbox alignments in preferences.ui
  * l10n: Update POT
    Remove obsolete options
  * Split APT cache refresh away from checkAPT (#496)
  * Add CI and dummy test (#493)
  * Remove levels (#492)
  * Revert "Fix root refresh creating root owned files and on LMDE ignoring
    settings (#472)"
  * Change datetime import (#487)
  * Fix infobar icon
  * Remove debug and indentation leftover
  * Fix datetime.now() calls
  * Fix generate_desktop_files
  * Remove unused import
  * Inject the app version during the build
  * Small fixes to the previous commit
  * l10n: Rephrase msgids for blacklist options
  * CheckWarnings: Fix package names appearing more than once

